  "instruction": "Create a very simple Generative UI check project in VS Code. Create folder /home/user/Desktop/generative_ui_quick with two files: index.html and manifest.json. In index.html, include a main container with id=\"app\", a hero section with id=\"hero\", and a button with id=\"cta\" whose text is exactly \"Start\". Also include the page title text \"Generative UI Quick Check\" somewhere in the HTML body. In manifest.json, set project to \"generative-ui-quick\", theme to \"mint\", and version to \"1.0\". Save both files and make a zip file /home/user/Desktop/generative_ui_quick_bundle.zip containing index.html and manifest.json.",
  "source": "authors | sanity bundle for UI generation smoke validation",
